content:
Use keyboard shortcuts to work more efficiently with macros.

REQUIRED EDITIONS

Available in: Professional, Enterprise, Performance, Unlimited, and Developer Editions (Classic), Essentials, Professional, Enterprise, Performance, Unlimited, and Developer Editions (Lightning)

Macro Utility Shortcuts in Lightning Experience
COMMAND	DESCRIPTION	SHORTCUT
Open and close Macro utility	Opens and closes the macro utility.	M
Run macro	Use this shortcut when a macro is selected or your search results return one item.	Enter
Navigate list of macros	Arrow keys

Macro Builder Shortcuts in Lightning Experience
COMMAND	DESCRIPTION	SHORTCUT
Global
Save	Saves the macro and its instructions.	Windows: Ctrl+S, macOS: Cmd+S
Display shortcut menu	Launches the shortcut menu.	Windows: Ctrl+/, macOS: Cmd+/
Switch panel focus	F6
Canvas
Select focused element	Spacebar or Enter
Switch focus to next element	Tab
Switch focus to previous element	Shift+Tab

Macro Shortcuts in Salesforce Classic
COMMAND	DESCRIPTION	SHORTCUT
Open Macro widget	Opens the Macro widget.	M
Go to macro search	Moves cursor to search bar.	S
Edit macro	Edit the selected macro.	E
View macro	View the Macro Details page.	V
Run macro	Run the selected macro.	Enter
View macro instruction	Expands or collapses the macroâ€™s instruction.	Spacebar
Navigate macro list	Up Arrow, Down Arrow
title: Keyboard Shortcuts for Macros in Service Cloud
